Participants number 111 and 141 are excluded from the analysis due to medication consumption that might affect result interpretation.

#Directory change to target folder
cd /Users/shirai/Desktop/gut-microbiota-analysis/250819_healthy-adult_qiime2-2024.5

#qiime2-amplicon-2024.5 activation
conda activate qiime2-amplicon-2024.5

#Casava 1.8 paired-end demultiplexed fastq
In Casava 1.8 demultiplexed (paired-end) format, there are two fastq.gz files for each sample in the study,
each containing the forward or reverse reads for that sample. The file name includes the sample identifier.
The forward and reverse read file names for a single sample might look like L2S357_15_L001_R1_001.fastq.gz and L2S357_15_L001_R2_001.fastq.gz, respectively.
The underscore-separated fields in this file name are: the sample identifier, the barcode sequence or a barcode identifier,
the lane number, the direction of the read (i.e. R1 or R2), and the set number.

#Importing demultiplexed data that follows some common formatting conventions (the Casava formats)
qiime tools import \
--type 'SampleData[PairedEndSequencesWithQuality]' \
--input-path #insert-directory: e.g. /Users/shirai/Desktop/gut-microbiota-analysis/250819_healthy-adult_qiime2-2024.5/fastq \
--input-format CasavaOneEightSingleLanePerSampleDirFmt \
--output-path demux-paired-end.qza

#Visualization of demux-paired-end.qza
qiime demux summarize \
--i-data demux-paired-end.qza \
--o-visualization demux-paired-end.qzv
